When the user says "release", "tag", "publish version", or asks to ship
recent work, read the full playbook in
`.ai/skills/release-new-version/SKILL.md` and follow it end-to-end.

## The non-obvious bits to not forget

- `composer.json` does **not** carry a `version` field — the git tag is
  the source of truth.
- `dist/js/tool.js` and `dist/js/tool.css` are committed on purpose;
  rebuild and stage them in the same commit as the source change before
  tagging.
- Public surface for SemVer purposes: contracts in `src/Contracts/`,
  JSON resources in `src/Http/Resources/`, route paths in
  `routes/api.php`, config keys in `config/nova-chat.php`, and the
  migration stub in `database/stubs/`. Anything else is internal.
- After tagging, confirm Packagist picked up the new version at
  `https://packagist.org/packages/asciisd/nova-chat` (or click
  **Update** there).
